    • Class com.paiondata.aristotle.model.dto.FilterQueryGraphDTO

      class FilterQueryGraphDTO extends BaseEntity implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • pageNumber
          Integer pageNumber
          The page number of the result set. Defaults to 1.
        • pageSize
          Integer pageSize
          The number of results per page. Defaults to 10.
        • properties
          Map<String,String> properties
          The filtering criteria on the requested graph. The criteria is a JSON object with non-nested key-value pairs. Each key represents an attribute name, and each value represents the attribute value to filter by. For example, to filter nodes by name and graduation status, you can use: { "name": "Peter", "graduated": "false" } If the filter parameters are empty, all data will be queried.
          See Also:
          • Aristotle WS Documentation for more details.
        • uuid
          @NotBlank(message="uuid must not be blank!") String uuid
          The uuid of the graph.

      • Serialized Fields

          List<NodeVO> nodes
          The nodes.

          The relations between nodes.

    • Class com.paiondata.aristotle.model.dto.NodeDTO

      class NodeDTO extends BaseEntity implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • properties
          Map<String,String> properties
          The attributes of the node.

          This field is a map where the keys are the names of the attributes and the values are the corresponding attribute values.

          For example, if you want to set the name of the node to "Peter" and the age to "30", the map would look like this: 

           {
   "name": "Peter",
   "age": "30"
 }

          Note that the values are stored as strings, so you may need to convert them to the appropriate data type when using them.

        • temporaryId
          @NotBlank(message="temporaryId must not null!") String temporaryId
          The temporary identifier of the node.

          This field is required and must not be blank. It serves as a temporary identifier for the node during the creation process.

          See Also:
          • Message.TEMPORARY_ID_MUST_NOT_NULL

    • Class com.paiondata.aristotle.model.dto.NodeUpdateDTO

      class NodeUpdateDTO extends BaseEntity implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • graphUuid
          @NotBlank(message="uuid must not be blank!") String graphUuid
          The unique identifier (UUID) of the graph.
        • properties
          Map<String,String> properties
          The attributes of the node.

          This field is a map of node attributes. Each key in the map represents an attribute name, and the corresponding value represents the attribute value. These attributes can include any relevant information about the node.

          Note: This is an overwrite operation. The attributes provided will overwrite the existing attributes of the node. If you want to update only specific attributes, you must provide all the attributes you want to keep, including the ones you are not changing.

          Key: The name of the attribute (e.g., "name", "age").

          Value: The value of the attribute (e.g., "Peter", "30").

        • uuid
          @NotBlank(message="uuid must not be blank!") String uuid
          The unique identifier (UUID) of the node.

          This field is the unique identifier for the node. It is typically a UUID and is used to reference the node in other parts of the system.

          Note: This field is required and must not be blank.

          See Also:
          • Message.UUID_MUST_NOT_BE_BLANK

    • Class com.paiondata.aristotle.model.dto.RelationUpdateDTO

      class RelationUpdateDTO extends BaseEntity implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • deleteList
          List<String> deleteList
          A list of identifiers of relations to be deleted.

          This field is a list of identifiers of the relations that need to be deleted from the graph. Each identifier in the list corresponds to a specific relation.

          Note: This field is optional. If not provided, no relations will be deleted.

        • graphUuid
          @NotBlank(message="uuid must not be blank!") String graphUuid
          The unique identifier (UUID) of the graph where the relations will be updated.

          This field is the unique identifier for the graph. It is typically a UUID and is used to reference the graph in other parts of the system.

          Note: This field is required and must not be blank.

          See Also:
          • Message.UUID_MUST_NOT_BE_BLANK
        • updateMap
          Map<String,String> updateMap
          A map containing the updates to be applied to the relations.

          This field is a map where each key represents the identifier of a relation, and the corresponding value represents the updated value of the relation. The updates provided will overwrite the existing values of the relations.

          Note: This is an overwrite operation. The values provided will overwrite the existing values of the relations. If you want to update only specific attributes, you must provide all the attributes you want to keep, including the ones you are not changing.

          Key: The identifier of the relation ("relation1", "relation2").

          Value: The updated value of the relation ("new_value1", "new_value2").
